00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:38,620
and this is his reactor,

396
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:41,460
he was at the Jet Propulsion Laboratory in Pasadena,

397
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:44,500
and this is a little bit of Lost City behind him,

398
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:46,700
and essentially what he was arguing,

399
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:50,900
and what I still think to be the right way of seeing the question,

400
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:53,620
is that there are high concentrations of hydrogen

401
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:55,580
in these alkaline fluids,

402
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:57,380
bubbling up into the ocean,

403
00:20:57,380 --> 00:21:00,980
and the oceans, the early oceans were CO2 rich,

404
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:02,820
it's very hard to constrain how much,

405
00:21:02,820 --> 00:21:06,780
but probably as much as one bar of carbon dioxide in those early oceans,

406
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:10,500
they would have been mildly acidic, perhaps pH 5 or 6,

407
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:16,380
and that means this is the sponge-like,

408
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:18,140
mineralised sponge-like structure,

409
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:21,420
all of these interconnected micro pores.

410
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,780
Four billion years ago, before there was any oxygen,

411
00:21:23,780 --> 00:21:25,740
this is now carbonate rocks,

412
00:21:25,740 --> 00:21:28,820
but we would expect to see lots of iron and nickel

413
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:30,620
and transition metals in there as well,

414
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:32,660
because these dissolved in the oceans

415
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,540
before there was any oxygen around,

416
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:36,420
especially in acidic oceans.

417
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,740
So we would expect to see some of these walls

418
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:43,740
effectively containing catalytic transition metals and equivalents.

419
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:46,220
And so reactive fluids percolating,

420
00:21:46,220 --> 00:21:48,700
wending their way through, ocean waters coming in,

421
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:53,380
this is really an electrochemical flow reactor,

422
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:56,140
where we've got the two components that I was saying earlier on,

423
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:57,460
make up the Krebs cycle,

